{
  "texts": [
    "[152] utilized the API2Vec model, inspired by Word2Vec, to embed APIs into high-dimensional vectors for cross-language code translation.",
    "Chen et al. [153] introduced BigPT, a technique for interactive cross-language retrieval from Big Code, involving a predictive transformation model based on auto-encoders to aid program translation using retrieved code representations.",
    "Users are able to further refine the retrieval results to improve the process.",
    "DatasetsThe following datasets in Table 7 [154,176,182,187,202,211,212] are commonly used for natural language based code search.The StaQC dataset [130] is tailored for predicting the suitability of code snippets in addressing specific queries.",
    "Comprising (question, code) pairs, it was curated by filtering Python and SQL Stack Overflow posts tagged with \"how-to\" questions, resulting in 147546 Python pairs and 119519 SQL pairs."
  ]
}